  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The power-law hemolysis damage model has not been validated against high-shear transient exposures shorter than 10 ms; this edge case is not fully covered by the validation dataset. The assessment team notes that the risk is acceptable, but no formal explanation of why this residual risk is tolerable for CPB use has been recorded.",
