      "name": "Steady-state hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD predictions of the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro measurements for the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump across 5 operating points. Agreement within 15% for all points meeting MRL 2 output comparison requirements. Known limitation: validation corpus covers exposure durations of 10 ms and above only; sub-10 ms high-shear transient events present in gap regions were not represented in the experimental dataset used. The assessment team has flagged this as a known limitation and considers the risk acceptable."
