      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s) and density (1056 kg/m³) taken from FDA benchmark specification. Hemolysis model coefficients (C=3.62×10⁻⁵, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785) sourced from Giersiepen et al. and confirmed against Heuser and Opitz calibration dataset. Parametric sensitivity to ±10% coefficient variation shows less than 6% change in NIH, within acceptance band."
