    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per the MRL 2 factor matrix. Validation against the FDA benchmark dataset demonstrates CFD prediction of NIH within 15% across all operating points. The power-law hemolysis model has a known limitation regarding sub-10 ms high-shear transient exposures that were not covered by the validation dataset; the assessment team considers this risk acceptable. The model is therefore considered credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, and the credibility assessment is Accepted.",
